cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.RO, cs.CR, cs.AI 

The paper proposes an approach to detect collision-prone vehicle behavior at intersections using a deep learning model. The approach involves analyzing the interaction trajectories of vehicles at intersections, which can be considered as a computer vision problem (cs.CV). The proposed model is a Siamese Interaction Long Short-Term Memory network (SILSTM), which is a type of recurrent neural network (RNN) used for sequence modeling and prediction. Therefore, the paper is likely to belong to the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG) and robotics (cs.RO). The paper also involves analyzing accident characteristics and labeling interaction trajectories as safe or unsafe, which can be considered as a cybersecurity (cs.CR) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) problem.
